      "Physical keys have a home and a log: held in the office key cabinet (locked, access-controlled), signed out for the run or shift with time and signature, signed back the same day, with overnight holding only under documented standing arrangements (the 6am first call) reviewed periodically — and unexplained key absence treated as a live incident, not a note for the next audit",
      "Keysafe discipline is trained as habit: approach checked (who's watching), code entered shielded, key used, key returned, safe CLOSED and SCRAMBLED — the unscrambled safe is an open door with extra steps — and safes themselves police-preferred models where the service advises on installation, sited with thought (not lit by the streetlamp beside the front path)",
